002 \u2013 \"Les motets\", Ensemble Musica Nova, Lucien Kandel, Zig-Zag Territoires 021002.2 (2 CDs)\n*2003 \u2013 ''Unrequited: Music of Guillaume de Machaut''. Liber unUsualis.\n*2004 \u2013 ''Machaut: Motets''. The Hilliard Ensemble\n*2004 \u2013  ''Ma fin est mon commencement'', by [[Louis Thiry]] (organ). Hortus records.\n*2009 \u2013 \"Ballades\", Ensemble Musica Nova, Lucien Kandel, AEON AECD 0982.\n*2010 \u2013 ''Art of Love: Music of Machaut'', [[Robert Sadin]], Edge Records, with [[Mark Feldman]], [[Hassan Hakmoun]], [[John Ellis (saxophonist)|John Ellis]], [[Lionel Loueke]], [[Brad Mehldau]], [[Milton Nascimento]].\n*2010 \u2013 \"Messe Notre-Dame\", (with Philippe de Vitry, Robertsbridge Codex, Pierre de Bruges, Gilles d'Orl\u00e9ans, Bernard de Cluny), Ensemble Musica Nova, Lucien Kandel, AEON AECD 1093.\n*2011 \u2013 ''Sacred And Secular Music: Messe De Nostre Dame'' [Dominique Vellard: Ensemble Gilles Binchois], Brilliant Classics 94217 [Licensed from Cantus Records].\n*2013 \u2013 ''Machaud: Mon chant vous envoy''. Various Artists. Eloquentia Records EL1342.\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Poetry}}\n*[[List of compositions by Guillaume de Machaut]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Earp | first1 = Lawrence | year = 1989 | title = Machaut's Role in the Production of Manuscripts of His Works | url = | journal = Journal of the American Musicological Society | volume = 42 | issue = | pages = 461\u2013503 | doi=10.1525/jams.1989.42.3.03a00020 <ref=harv}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Hanly|2000}}|reference=Hanly, Michael. \"France\", from ''A Companion to Chaucer'', ed. Peter Brown, {{Page needed|date=March 2020|reason=Inclusive pages of Hanly's chapter are needed}} (Oxford: Blackwell, 2000).}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Keitel|1982}}|reference=Keitel, Elizabeth. \"The So-called Cyclic Mass of Guillame De Machaut: New Evidence for an Old Debate\", ''The Musical Quarterly'', Vol. 68, no. 3 (1982). pp.&nbsp;307\u2013323.}}\n* 