16-7}}; {{ISBN|978-1-84383-016-0}}\n* Leach, Elizabeth Eva. ''Guillaume de Machaut: Secretary, Poet, Musician'' (Cornell University Press, 2011). {{ISBN|978-0-8014-4933-8}}\n* Leech-Wilkinson, Daniel (ed.). ''La Messe de Nostre Dame'' (Oxford and New York: Oxford University Press, 1990).\n* Leech-Wilkinson, Daniel. ''Machaut's Mass: An Introduction'' (Oxford and New York: Oxford University Press, 1992).\n* Ludwig, Friedrich (ed.), [http://www.free-scores.com/download-sheet-music.php?pdf=35322 ''Guillaume de Machaut: musikalische Werke. Erster Band: Balladen, Rondeux und Virelais''], Publikationen \u00e4lterer Musik, 1 (Leipzig: Breitkopf & H\u00e4rtel).\n*{{cite web |title=The Works of Guillaume de Machaut|url=http://www.lib.latrobe.edu.au/MMDB/composer/COM003.htm |publisher=[[La Trobe University]] Library |date=2003-06-02|accessdate=2008-02-08}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Zayaruznaya|first1=Anna|title=The Monstrous New Art: Divided Forms in the Late Medieval Motet|date=2015|publisher=Cambridge University Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=COJwBwAAQBAJ|accessdate=15 July 2015}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Wikisource1911Enc|Machaut, Guillaume de}}\n* {{Britannica|354543}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Guillaume de Machaut}}\n*[http://www.medieval.org/emfaq/composers/machaut.html Guillaume de Machaut FAQ and discography]\n*{{ChoralWiki}}\n*Free access to high-resolution [http://www.diamm.ac.uk/ images of manuscripts] containing works by Machaut from Digital Image Archive of Medieval Music\n*{{IMSLP|id=Machaut, Guillaume de|cname=Guillame de Machaut}}\n*Listen to [http://www.acc.umu.se/~akadkor/early/IID_Machaut_Guillaume_de.html free recordings of songs] from ([http://www.acc.umu.se/~akadkor/indexENG.html Ume\u00e5 Akademiska K\u00f6r]).\n*Images of the Ferrell-Vog\u00fc\u00e9 MS, a major collection of the poetry and music of Machaut: [http://www.diamm.ac.uk The Digital Image Archive of Medieval Music].\n*[http://www.classicis